  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Landmine victims in Quang Binh, Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Quang Binh province has about 19,928 landmine victims. Most of them are living in rural and mountainous areas with poor economic conditions. In addition, landmine accidents more or less affect their ability to work. Therefore, it&apos;s difficult for them to obtain a stable job with income. Without a sustainable economic base, they are also limited in accessing health care service. The project hopes to empower landmine victims to increase their income, self-sustainability and social participation.</narrative>
  </description>
